Package comp3111.input.validators

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DateAvailableInTourValidator
    Validates whether a date is available for use in a tour.
    DateIsEarlierThanOfferingLastEditableDateValidator
    Validates whether the date is earlier than an offering's last editable date, as in when creating an offering, it validates whether the date is allowed or not
    DateNotEarlierThanValidator
    Validates whether a date is earlier than another date.
    DoubleLowerBoundValidator
    Validates whether a double value is higher than a lower bound value
    DoubleRangeValidator
    Validates whether a double value is within a range
    HKIDValidator
    Validates whether a given HKID is valid or not
    IntegerLowerBoundedByAnotherFieldValidator
    Validates an integer value with a user inputted lower bound from a textfield
    IntegerLowerBoundValidator
    Validates whether an integer value is larger than a lower bound or not
    IntegerRangeValidator
    Validates whether an integer is within a range or not
    ListOfDatesValidator
    Validates Tour creation, for a limited tour type, it needs a number of dates.
    OfferingStillOpenValidator
    Validates whether an offering is still open for new applications (has it gone over the last possible day of booking or not)
    PhoneNumberValidator
    Validates whether a string is a valid phone number string or not
    ReturnValidationErrorWithLogging
    A class that logs all incidents of errors during validation
    StringDoesNotContainSubstringValidator
    Validates that a string does not contain a substring
    StringLengthCanNullValidator
    Validates if a string is within a certain length, number inclusive
    StringLengthValidator
    Validates if a string is within a certain length, number inclusive
    StringNotEqualsToIgnoreCaseValidator
    Validates that a string is not equal to a specified string, ignoring case
    TourGuideAvailableForDatesValidater
    Validates whether a tour guide is available between a certain date range.
    ValidatorFactory
    A factory class that creates an instance of the validators when requested.
